The figure for Ottoman casualties in the battle varied according to the sources, just like the figure for Crusader casualties.  To present an objective view its necessary to provide the full range of figures the sources named, not just the lowest casualty count recorded.
Added the full range of Ottoman casualties reported in the sources.  It was only fair that the full range of numbers was given, since the same practice was applied to the Crusaders' casualties too.

Occhiali was beylerbey of the Regency of Algiers, which participated with 14 galleys and was positionned in the left Ottoman flank, it led the the assault against the maltese ships under Andrea Doria and would play a crucial role in saving the remaining Ottoman fleet from complete destruction, the Ottoman empire from then on relied more on barbary corsairs in its wars with venice and other maritime european powers.
